  "prompt": "How do I install software on Ubuntu?",
  "response": "There are several ways to install software on Ubuntu:\n\n1. Ubuntu Software Center (GUI method)\n- Open Ubuntu Software Center\n- Search for the application\n- Click \"Install\"\n\n2. APT Package Manager (Command line)\n- Open Terminal\n- Use command: sudo apt update\n- Install software with: sudo apt install [package-name]\nExample: sudo apt install firefox\n\n3. Snap Packages\n- Many applications can be installed using Snap\n- Command: sudo snap install [package-name]\nExample: sudo snap install spotify\n\n4. .deb Package Installation\n- Download .deb file from website\n- Double-click to open with Ubuntu Software\n- Click \"Install\"\n- Or use terminal: sudo dpkg -i [filename.deb]\n\n5. PPA (Personal Package Archive)\n- Add repository: sudo add-apt-repository [ppa-name]\n- Update: sudo apt update\n- Install: sudo apt install [package-name]\n\n6. Flatpak\n- Install Flatpak first: sudo apt install flatpak\n- Add Flathub repository\n- Install packages: flatpak install [package-name]\n\nChoose the method that best suits your needs and comfort level.",
